Who's News:
   Ross Quits BP America
   For Cable  Wireless
   ----
   Special to The Wall Street Journal
The 53-year-old Mr. Ross had wanted to return to the U.K.
in a senior, chief executive position, industry executives
said.
   BP America also said Sir Campbell Fraser and Ray Knowland
will retire from the board March 20. The board of the U.S.
unit intends to appoint Mr. Chase and Steve Ahearne managing
directors to fill their seats. It also intends to appoint
Karen N. Horn a non-executive director, effective March 21,
and Bryan Sanderson a managing director, effective April 17,
once approval is given to raise the number of directors.